01/09/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- About 200 people took part in a peaceful march through Sarajevo on Monday (August 31st) to raise public awareness regarding the fate of missing persons 14 years after the end of the 1992-1995 conflict.
An estimated 10,000 people are still missing in BiH.
The protesters called for an agreement among BiH, Croatia and Serbia to exchange information and co-operate in the search.
In other news, a three-day regional conference titled "Transparency of Courts and Media Responsibility" opened in Sarajevo on Tuesday.
Topics relate to war crimes proceedings, judicial transparency and objective and reliable reporting on crimes committed during the conflicts of the 1990s.
More than 60 people from the region, as well as representatives of The Hague war crimes tribunal, international NGOs and media are attending.
(RTRS, Srna, BHRT, Fena, Oslobodjenje - 31/08/09)
